      <h2>Introduction</h2>
      <p><b>
        Rohit Sharma is an Indian cricketer known for his elegant batting style and extraordinary batting records. He was born on April 30, 1987, in Nagpur, Maharashtra.
      </b></p>
     
      <h2>Early Life and Career</h2>
      <p><b>
        Rohit Sharma showed promising cricketing skills from a young age and made his debut for the Indian national team in 2007. He gained recognition as a talented middle-order batsman and later evolved into one of the finest openers in limited-overs cricket.
      </b></p>
     
      <h2>International Career</h2>
      <p><b>
        Rohit Sharma has achieved great success in international cricket. He holds multiple records, including the highest individual score in One Day Internationals (ODIs) with his incredible 264 runs against Sri Lanka. He has been a key player in India's victories in major tournaments like the ICC Champions Trophy and the Asia Cup.
      </b></p>
     
      <h2>Achievements</h2>
      <ul><b>
        <li>Holder of numerous batting records in international cricket</li>
        <li>Winner of multiple ICC tournaments with the Indian team</li>
        <li>Recipient of several awards and accolades</li>
      </b></ul>
     
      <h2>Quotes</h2>
      <blockquote><b>
        "I don't just want to be remembered as a good cricketer; I want to be remembered as a good person as well." - <b><u>Rohit Sharma</u></b>
      </b></blockquote>
